CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, November 29, 1958, page 4, reads: "With New Prexy - This group of local and visiting members of the National Association of Intergroup Relations Officials are shown with Margaret Garrity, of Chicago, Ill., NAIRO's new president. Left to right: Henry D. McCullough, Pennsylvania State Employment Service; Geroge Culberson, Pittsburgh Commission on Human Relations and NAIRO vice president; Frederick B. Routh, Southern Regional Council and NAIRO president-elect, Miss Garrity, Calvin D. Banks, Philadelphia NAACP; Mrs. Jesmine B. Merrill, Trenton, N. J., NAIRO secretary, and Arnold Aronson, NAIRO immediate past president. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Pennsylvania State Employment Service Henry D. McCullough, Pittsburgh Commission on Human Relations and NAIRO vice president Geroge Culberson, Southern Regional Council and NAIRO president-elect Frederick B. Merrill, and NAIRO past president Arnold Aronson, gathered for 12th annual National Association of Intergroup Relations Officials
